SEC Sanctions Direct Edge Exchanges, Broker Over Losses, Outages

-- B y   G r e g o r y   M o t t
-- 
2011-10-13T20:42:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/sec-sanctions-direct-edge-exchanges-broker-over-losses-outages.html
The U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission sanctioned two electronic  stock exchanges  and a
broker-dealer owned by Direct Edge Holdings LLC for violations
stemming from weak internal controls that resulted in millions
of dollars in trading losses and a systems outage.  The SEC announced the sanctions today in an e-mail
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Mott in Washington at 
 gmott1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
 lroberts13@bloomberg.net  